(1) Any person who has in his possession property which to his actual or constructive knowledge constitutes, in whole or in part, the proceeds of any property which was directly or indirectly acquired as a result of— (a) a crime committed under this Act; or (b) an act which, if it had been committed in Zambia, would have constituted an offence under this Act; shall be guilty of an offence and shall be liable upon conviction to imprisonment for a term not exceeding ten years.
