(1) Any drug enforcement officer or police officer may, subject to subsections (2) and (3), use a firearm issued to him against— (a) any person in lawful custody charged with or convicted of an offence relating to narcotic drugs or psychotropic substances when such person is escaping or attempting to escape; (b) any person who by force rescues or attempts to rescue any other person from lawful custody; (c) any person who by force prevents or attempts to prevent the lawful arrest of himself or of any other person: Provided that a drug enforcement officer or police officer shall not use a firearm unless the use of the firearm and the degree to which it is used is reasonable in the circumstances.
