(1) Where the High Court is satisfied that any property forfeited— (a) cannot be located or traced; (b) has been sold to a purchaser in good faith for valuable consideration; (c) is outside Zambia; (d) has been mingled with other property which cannot be separated or divided without difficulty; or (e) has been diminished in value; the High Court shall order that any other property of a similar value be forfeited.
